=========================================================
INTERVIEW READY ANSWER
=========================================================

An Abstract Class is a class that contains at least one pure virtual
function and cannot be instantiated. It is used to achieve abstraction,
provide common functionality and state to derived classes, and enforce
certain behaviors while enabling runtime polymorphism.

